`crates/ctx-context/tests/` is the integration-test surface for the whole
crate's public runtime behavior — chain resolution/rendering and the
hook/session/CLI dedup pipeline — exercised only against an in-memory
fake filesystem, never real disk I/O.

Both files share the same `FakeEnv` pattern: a flat `BTreeMap<String,
Vec<u8>>` keyed by repo-relative path, with directory-ness inferred from
key-prefix matching rather than stored explicitly. Any change to how
`Env::is_dir` or path lookups are implemented in the main crate must stay
compatible with this prefix-inference convention, or both test files
break simultaneously. Seeded tree shapes differ per file (chain_serve.rs
builds its own ad hoc trees per test; hook_session.rs uses one fixed
`FakeEnv::seeded()` layout reused across tests), so there's no shared
fixture to update in lockstep — each file's seeding is self-contained.

chain_serve.rs pins the traversal contract of `serve::chain_for`/`render`
(ordering, soft-missing markers, path-escape rejection). hook_session.rs
pins the session-dedup contract spanning `hook::run`, `session`
persistence, and `cli::dispatch`, including the on-disk session file path
template and fail-open behavior on corrupt state. Together they mean any
change to chain traversal order, session file path format, or dedup
keying must update tests in both files if the change touches shared code
paths (e.g., `chain_for` used inside `hook::run`).

No intent.md is present for this directory.